            </div>

            <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none mb-8">
              <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
                As a business owner, your time is valuable. Why get bogged down with routine tasks when you could focus on growth and innovation? Virtual assistants (VAs) offer an efficient solution, handling tasks like scheduling, email management, and social media, so you can concentrate on what really matters.
              </p>

              <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
                With numerous VA platforms available, finding remote help has never been easier. Skip the headaches of onboarding and payroll-most services offer a simple, flat-rate model, taking care of everything from HR to taxes. Whether you need administrative support, marketing expertise, or customer service, there's a VA service that fits your needs.
              </p>

              <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-8">
                We've reviewed the top virtual assistant services, evaluating pricing, skills, and industry expertise, to help you make the best choice for your business.
              </p>

              <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-6">Categories</h2>

              <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-12">
                <button class="bg-purple-400 hover:bg-purple-500 text-white font-semibold py-4 px-6 rounded-lg transition-colors">
                  Best for leveraging AI over human interaction
                </button>
                <button class="bg-purple-400 hover:bg-purple-500 text-white font-semibold py-4 px-6 rounded-lg transition-colors">
                  Best for Enterprise-Level Support
                </button>
                <button class="bg-purple-400 hover:bg-purple-500 text-white font-semibold py-4 px-6 rounded-lg transition-colors">
                  Best Quality of Assistants
                </button>
                <button class="bg-purple-400 hover:bg-purple-500 text-white font-semibold py-4 px-6 rounded-lg transition-colors">
                  Best for Specialized Services
                </button>
                <button class="bg-purple-400 hover:bg-purple-500 text-white font-semibold py-4 px-6 rounded-lg transition-colors">
                  Best Budget Option
                </button>
                <button class="bg-purple-400 hover:bg-purple-500 text-white font-semibold py-4 px-6 rounded-lg transition-colors">
                  Best for US-based Virtual Assistants
                </button>
              </div>

              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-4">Best for leveraging AI over human interaction</h3>
              <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-6">Magic</h2>

              <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-8 mb-8 flex items-center justify-center border border-gray-200">
                <img
                  src="/images/resources-page/the-best-va-services/magic.webp"
                  alt="Magic Logo"
                  class="w-full max-w-[520px] h-auto object-contain"
                  style="aspect-ratio: 1100/520;"
                />
              </div>

              <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
                Magic offers executive assistant services with a focus on executive support, customer service, and general administrative tasks. Each assistant utilizes proprietary software and AI tools, including ChatGPT, for various tasks such as strategic planning, image creation, programming, and document summarization. While clients have access to a dedicated account manager and 24/7 support, the primary support model is text-based, leveraging AI extensively, which may not suit all business needs. For those who prefer minimal human interaction, the model may be particularly appealing.
              </p>

              <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
                Magic has an additional product called Magic 24/7 which lets customers delegate work to a team of trained assistants available 24 hours a day. This service costs $35 per hour spent on the task, but you get 20 hours per month included if you have a full-time Executive Assistant service.
              </p>

